----#include Global
----#include Utils
function getObjectsOnTop(objectPos)
    return Physics.cast({
        origin = objectPos,
        direction = {0, 1, 0},
        size = {x = 0.1, y = 0.1, z = 0.1},
        max_distance = 0.1,
        type = 1, --Ray cast
        debug = true
    })
end

function isCard(object)
    return object ~= nil and object.tag == "Card"
end

function isDeck(object)
    return object ~= nil and object.tag == "Deck"
end

function stackOnTop(object, times)
    pos = object.getPosition()
    for i = 1, times do
        object.clone({position = pos})
    end
end

----#include Const\Const
----#include SetupSupplyDecks
function checkSupplyDecks()
    result = {}
    for i, guid in pairs(const.game.supplies) do
        deck_board = getObjectFromGUID(guid)
        if deck_board == nil then
            return false, result, "Missing GUID:" .. guid
        end
        objectsOnTop = getObjectsOnTop(deck_board.getPosition())
        if(#objectsOnTop ~= 1)then return false, result, "Missing or wrong card on deck board:" .. i end
        card = objectsOnTop[1].hit_object
        if(not isCard(card)) then return false, result, "Missing or wrong card on deck:" .. i end
        result[#result + 1] = card
    end
    return true, result
end

function dealStartCards(stack, amount)
    for color, _ in pairs(const.player) do
        if(Player[color].seated)then
            print("deal to " .. color)
            stack.deal(amount, color)
        end
    end
end

function setupStartCards()
    copperStack = getObjectFromGUID(const.game.stacks.treasure.copper)
    victoryStack = getObjectFromGUID(const.game.stacks.victory.estate)
    if(not isDeck(copperStack) or not isDeck(victoryStack)) then
        print("copper or estate stack not found")
        return
    end
    copperStack2 = copperStack.clone({position = {0, 10, 0}, callback_function = function(obj) dealStartCards(obj, 7) obj.destruct() end})
    copperStack2.use_gravity = false
    victoryStack2 = victoryStack.clone({position = {0, 20, 0}, callback_function = function(obj) dealStartCards(obj, 3) obj.destruct() end})
    victoryStack2.use_gravity = false
end


function SetupGame()
    isValid, cards, error = checkSupplyDecks()
    if(isValid)then
        setupStartCards()
        for _, card in pairs(cards) do
            stackOnTop(card, 9)
        end
    else
        print("SupplyDecksError: " .. error)
    end

end

function drawCardFromDeck(color)
    deckPos = getObjectFromGUID(const.player[color].deck).getPosition()
    deck = getObjectsOnTop(deckPos)[1]
    if(deck == nil)then
        print("(" .. color .. ") Deck is empty")
        moveCardsToDiscard(color)
        moveDiscardToDeck(color)
    else
        deck.hit_object.deal(1, color)
    end
end

function moveCardsToDiscard(color)
    -- TODO
end

function moveDiscardToDeck(color)
    discardPos = getObjectFromGUID(const.player[color].discard).getPosition()
    discard = getObjectsOnTop(discardPos)[1]
    if(discard == nil)then
        print("(" .. color .. ") Discard is empty")
    else
        discard = discard.hit_object
        deckPosition = getObjectFromGUID(const.player[color].deck).getPosition()
        discard.shuffle()
        discard.flip()
        discard.setPositionSmooth(deckPosition, true, false)
    end
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
A very small expansion that introduces the 'Potion' mechanic.
While the Potion cost cards themselves are fairly interesting/powerful and fun to play with, this is generally regarded as the worst expansion due to the Potions themselves.
Play this with an open mind, as there are some neat tricks up its sleeve. It just doesn't mix well with other expansions, unless half of the Kingdom is Alchemy.

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
Introduces 'Events', cards set out along with the supplies that can be bought for their effects during a Buy phase.
Also introduces 'Reserves', cards that are set aside when played, and be called again later on for an immediate effect.
There's also a slew of tokens that are utilized here.
Not complex, but definitely complicated just due to the sheer amount of options this expansion brings.

Introduces the 'Debt' mechanic, a new token/type of cost for cards, allowing you to incur debt for a card without spending money for it.
Another addition are 'Split Piles', supply piles with five copies of a card at the top, and five copies of a more powerful counterpart underneath.
Also features more Events, and a new variation called Landmarks, passive Events that earn you VP tokens.

These may only be payed off during the Buy Phase.

'Guilds' reintroduces the Coin tokens as Coffers, now functioning as money that can be held onto for later. It also introduces an overpaying feature on some cards that yield additional benefits based on what you overpay.

'Cornucopia' has a theme of cards that exploit variety in your deck. It also contains 'Prize cards', unusually powerful cards that are gained via the 'Tournament' card.
